<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920220-0102</DOCNO><DOCID>920220-0102.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Ross Quits BP America   For Cable andamp; Wireless   ----   Special to The Wall Street Journal</HL><DATE>02/20/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8</SO><CO>   BP CWP WNEWS</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)OIL-INTEGRATED MAJORS (OIL)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><NS>PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)NORTH AMERICA (NME)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   CLEVELAND -- BP America Inc., a unit of British PetroleumCo., said James H. Ross is resigning as chairman and chiefexecutive officer effective March 20 to join Cable andamp; WirelessPLC as chief executive.   Rodney F. Chase was named to succeed him, effective March21. Mr. Chase is currently chief executive, WesternHemisphere, for BP Exploration.</LP><TEXT>   The 53-year-old Mr. Ross had wanted to return to the U.K.in a senior, chief executive position, industry executivessaid.   BP America also said Sir Campbell Fraser and Ray Knowlandwill retire from the board March 20. The board of the U.S.unit intends to appoint Mr. Chase and Steve Ahearne managingdirectors to fill their seats. It also intends to appointKaren N. Horn a non-executive director, effective March 21,and Bryan Sanderson a managing director, effective April 17,once approval is given to raise the number of directors.</TEXT></DOC>